If they are calling Kong vs. Godzilla a "battle for the ages" and this looks awesome especially Rodan rotating in midair to fend off fighter jets then I can't wait for 2020 to come around.  I know now the reason it is soo dark, so we won't see the imperfections in the cgi's and all that crap.  That's why Kong Skull Island was such a breath of fresh air than Godzilla 2014. text: I keep watching these teasers and trailers, hoping to see some redeeming qualities for this movie. But nope. <sigh>  I didn't think it was possible to make a Godzilla film I wouldn't watch, especially after GMK:GMAOA but congratulations Legendary, you did it. You had the chance to make something special. Something amazing. Something every bit as awesome as the MCU. And you freaking blew it. Why would you just throw away the great start you had?  Godzilla 2014 was so good! A brand new chance for the American Godzilla after that ridiculous 1998 farce. Even Kong: Skull Island was good. Advancing the timelines and connecting the two characters. The end of credits trailer had be jumping up and down in my seat, so ready for a movie to introduce Rodan. One to introduce Mothra. Then the pinnacle, one to introduce the most iconic character outside of G himself, King Gidorah. And you clowns went and lumped all into one movie and in one fell swoop, destroyed the new American Godzilla's chances to be great.  Way to go. You should be as happy as Universal is about the success of their Dark Universe. Seeing what a terrific job they did with the Mummy remake.

But times have probably changed, and maybe they did get the rights, and maybe they are hiding him. Still, I LOVE Anguirus. He will and has always been my favorite Godzilla Character in the entire franchise. My second favorite is Mechagodzilla II, and my third is Burning Godzilla. text: As far as cinematic universes go here is how I rank them.  1. Monsterverse (I grew up on monster movies, so I love having the opportunity to see them on the big screen. Plus unlike other universes this one is short and sweet.) 2. Dceu (yes I know,  they can only make bad movies. But I have always liked dc over marvel as a kid so for me seeing a bad dc movie is better than not seeing a dc movie at all.) 3. Mcu ( I loved what they have done with their movies but the problem is i have been watching them from day one but after so many years I found them to be predictable. And I started watching them just so when infinity wars came out I would know what is going on, after that I lost interest.) 4. X men (I only watched xmen for wolverine. Now that he is dead the future x men films don't have my attention,  unless it's deadpool.  5. Shyamalan verse (I just ranked as number 5 because 1- 4 was taken.) 6. Transformers (Less humans more transformers. That is what is needed.) 7. Dark universe ( The mummy was the first and last of this franchise. I really liked where they were going but it was poorly delivered and strayed from what the original movie had, which makes dc look as successful as marvel. Russell Crow was awesome in it though. )

text: Since the Legendary films are a bit more grounded then the Toho films, I can imagine that Gigans representation in this era; would be that the dead Mother MUTO that was in Godzilla 2014 would be salvaged by some shadow government to wage war against neighboring countries. The MUTO would be outfitted with cybernetic enhancements and titanium hooks. Teflon ‚Äúarmor‚Äù so it cannot be detected by radar (since it‚Äôs head already has that curvature)  shoulder rocket attachments, and classic buzzsaw designed specifically to maim Kaiju. This would be the main antagonist in the stand alone RODAN movie.    The other Kaiju would also get their own film. Mothra would have a stand alone film. Set in the 1940 during WW2 their lay an island that was protected by the wind God and wind Godess. Anytime anyone approaches this small Japanese island a huge gust of wind would blow back the ships. This was caused by the protector of the island Mothra and her ‚Äúhusband‚Äù Batra flapping their wings. Mothra loved humanity but was protective of the islanders because they possess the power to telepathically speak with the Kaiju, but battra secretly hated all humans, believing them to be unworthy and inconsiderate. It especially annoyed him when they would have the nerve to summon a god.. Battra then makes himself known durning the War and actively reveals himself to the world and engages in the war. Mothra does not condone this as they are meant to be humble and keep themselves hidden only to protect the island villagers and that is all. Mothra then gets attacked by Battra and is left wounded. The islanders then summon another celestial god to aid them ‚ÄúKing Caesar‚Äù the 2 Kaiju team up against Battra, but Battra does a killing blow that was meant for Caesar, but Mothra is hit instead, Battra is struck with guilt for what he had done, and mourns the death of Mothra. Caesar then kills Battra while he is distracted. Caesar then communes with the villagers that Kaiju should be hidden from the world and let ‚Äúthe islanders ‚Äú humanity progress to the future, he then returns to the cave and slumbers only to be cuddling up around Mothras egg.  The third Stand Alone film would be about Godzilla. After the events of Godzilla vs Kong, humanity realizes that coexistence with Godzilla is possible, the appropriate ‚Äúhousing‚Äù just needs to be made. Their is a nuclear power plant constructed solely to ‚Äúfeed‚Äù Godzilla so that the radiation allows him to move his massive body because the cells are repairing/reinforcing themselves constantly just so he can get buy and not be sluggish. Later, the radiation that was provided makes Godzilla ill, where he vomits in the ocean, the radiation is raw and not concentrated, they negligently dispose of it in the ocean where it comes into contact with Godzilla‚Äôs vomits, oil that had failed to clean up, and floating trash. The chemical mixture ends up creating the smog monster aka hedorah, this is a mindless creature whose only intentions is to feed off of any radiation where it can aggressively grown in size. Since prolonged exposure to the creature causes nausea and vertigo due to its high radiation, Godzilla cannot combat it alone, the humans construct a mech called MOGUERA that ‚Äúcleans‚Äù radiation to aid Godzilla to fight it. Godzilla defeats Hedorah only to have a piece of the dorsal fin to break off. The smog monster ends up disintegrating, only to be mixed with Godzilla‚Äôs fin, where the next film would feature Biollante as the main antagonist. Biollantes body is spreading across the ocean floor where giant tendrils emerge on the main land. Once again, it is up to the earth Kaiju to team up Godzilla, Rodan, Mothra, With new faces King Kong, Anguirus, King Caesar, MOGUERA and it‚Äôs new upgraded counterpart Jet Jaguar to save the planet once more.
